In all, 50 H. diversicolor and 40 E. akaara were used in this study to test the correlation between the qRPA and qPCR assays. The detection percentage of samples infected with AbHV for both methods were 96% and 93%, respectively. The detection percentage of RGNNV was 97% and 95%, respectively. Additionally, these data show that there is a strong correlation between qRPA and qPCR detection (R2
 > 0.8) (Fig. 5
).
